obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2000)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2000&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Bhopal Gas Leak Disaster`
  line `(Processing of Claims) Act, 1985.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 20th day of February, 1985.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2001)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2001&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Bhopal gas leak disaster" or "disaster" means the occurrence on the 2nd and 3rd days of`
  line `December, 1984, which involved the release of highly noxious and abnormally dangerous gas from a`
  line `plant in Bhopal (being a plant of the Union Carbide India Limited, a subsidiary of the Union Carbide`
  line `Corporation, U.S.A.) and which resulted in loss of life and damage to property on an extensive scale;`
  line
  line `(b) "claim" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a claim, arising out of, or connected with, the disaster, for compensation or damages for`
  line `any loss of life or personal injury which has been, or is likely to be, suffered;`
  line
  line `(ii) a claim, arising out of, or connected with, the disaster, for any damage to property which`
  line `has been, or is likely to be, sustained;`
  line
  line `(iii) a claim for expenses incurred or required to be incurred for containing the disaster or`
  line `mitigating or otherwise coping with the effects of the disaster;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other claim (including any claim by way of loss of business or employment) arising`
  line `out of, or connected with, the disaster;`
  line
  line `(c) "claimant" means a person entitled to make a claim;`
  line
  line `(d) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner appointed under section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) "person" includes the Government;`
  line
  line `(f) "Scheme" means a Scheme framed under section 9.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of clauses (b) and (c), where the death of a person has taken`
  line `place as a result of the disaster, the claim for compensation or damages for the death of such person`
  line `shall be for the benefit of the spouse, children (including a child in the womb) and other heirs of the`
  line `deceased and they shall be deemed to be the claimants in respect thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2002)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of Central Government to represent claimants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2002&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government shall, and shall have the exclusive right to, represent, and act in place of`
  line `(whether within or outside India) every person who has made, or is entitled to make, a claim for all`
  line `purposes connected with such claim in the same manner and to the same effect as such person.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `purposes referred to therein include--`
  line
  line `(a) institution of any suit or other proceeding in or before any court or other authority (whether`
  line `within or outside India) or withdrawal of any such suit or other proceeding, and`
  line
  line `(b) entering into a compromise.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply also in relation to claims in respect of which suits or`
  line `other proceedings have been instituted in or before any court or other authority (whether within or outside`
  line `India) before the commencement of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any such suit or other proceeding with respect to any claim pending`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act in or before any court or other authority outside India,`
  line `the Central Government shall represent, and act in place of, or along with, such claimant, if such court or`
  line `other authority so permits.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2003)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Claimant’s right to be represented by a legal practitioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2003&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 3, in representing, and acting in place of, any person in relation to any claim, the`
  line `Central Government shall have due regard to any matters which such person may require to be urged with`
  line `respect to his claim and shall, if such person so desires, permit at the expense of such person, a legal`
  line `practitioner of his choice to be associated in the conduct of any suit or other proceeding relating to his`
  line claim.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2004)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2004&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of discharging its functions under this Act,`
  line `the Central Government shall have the powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person from any part of India and examining`
  line `him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line specify.
  line
  line `(2) Every notification made under clause (f) of sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the notification or both Houses agree that the notification should not be made,`
  line `the notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2005)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Commissioner and other officers and employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1992, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-8-1992)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2005&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of assisting it in`
  line `discharging its functions under this Act, the Central Government may appoint an officer, to be known as`
  line `the Commissioner for the welfare of the victims of the Bhopal gas leak disaster, and such other officers`
  line `and employees to assist him as that Government may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall discharge such functions as may be assigned to him by the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner and such of the officers subordinate to him as may be authorised by the`
  line `Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette in this behalf may, for the discharge of their`
  line `functions under the Scheme, exercise all or any of the powers which the Central Government may`
  line `exercise under section 5.`
  line
  line `(4) All officers and authorities of the Government shall act in aid of the Commissioner`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(5) The Commissioner and the officers subordinate to him authorised to discharge functions under`
  line `the Scheme shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2006)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-8-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2006&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `delegate, subject to such conditions and limitations as may be specified in the notification, all or any of its`
  line `powers under this Act (excepting the power under section 9 to frame a Scheme) to the Government of`
  line `Madhya Pradesh or an officer of the Central Government not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to that`
  line `Government or an officer of the Government of Madhya Pradesh not below the rank of a Secretary to that`
  line `Government ^1`
  line `[or the Commissioner].`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2007)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2007&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) In computing, under the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963) or any other law for`
  line `the time being in force, the period of limitation for the purpose of instituting a suit or other proceeding for`
  line `the enforcement of a claim, any period after the date on which such claim is registered under, and in`
  line `accordance with, the provisions of the Scheme shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to any proceedings by way of appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2008)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to frame a Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2008&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for carrying into effect the`
  line `purposes of this Act, frame by notification in the Official Gazette a Scheme as soon as may be after the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), a Scheme`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the registration of the claims under the Scheme and all matters connected with such`
  line registration;
  line
  line `(b) the processing of the claims for securing their enforcement and matters connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(c) the maintenance of records and registers in respect of the claims;`
  line
  line `(d) the creation of a fund for meeting expenses in connection with the administration of the`
  line `Scheme and of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the amounts which the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament`
  line `by law in that behalf, credit to the fund referred to in clause (d) and any other amounts which may be`
  line `credited to such fund;`
  line
  line `(f) the utilisation, by way of disbursal (including apportionment) or otherwise, of any amounts`
  line `received in satisfaction of the claims;`
  line
  line `(g) the officer (being a judicial officer of a rank not lower than that of a District Judge) who may`
  line `make such disbursal or apportionment in the event of a dispute;`
  line
  line `(h) the maintenance and audit of accounts with respect to the amounts referred to in clauses(e)`
  line `and (f);`
  line
  line `(i) the functions of the Commissioner and other officers and employees appointed under section`
  line 6.
  line
  line `(3) Every Scheme framed under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is framed,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the Scheme or both Houses agree that the Scheme should not be framed, the Scheme shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that Scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2009)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Removal of doubts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2009&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that--`
  line
  line `(a) any sums paid by the Government to a claimant otherwise than by way of disbursal of the`
  line `compensation or damages received as a result of the adjudication or settlement of his claim by a court`
  line `or other authority, shall be deemed to be without prejudice to the adjudication or settlement by such`
  line `court or other authority of his claim to receive compensation or damages in satisfaction of his claim`
  line `and shall not be taken into account by such court or other authority in determining the amount of`
  line `compensation or damages to which he may be entitled in satisfaction of his claim;`
  line
  line `(b) in disbursing under the Scheme the amount received by way of compensation or damages in`
  line `satisfaction of a claim as a result of the adjudication or settlement of the claim by a court or other`
  line `authority, deduction shall be made from such amount of the sums, if any, paid to the claimant by the`
  line `Government before the disbursal of such amount.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (2010)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2010&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act and of any Scheme framed thereunder shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act or`
  line `any instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (2011)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754&sectionId=2011&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00012_198521_1517807326754
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bhopal Gas Leak Disaster (Processing of Claims) Ordinance, 1985`
  line `(1 of 1985),is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
